{
  "id": 5184267522015232,
  "name": "CSS Name-only Container Queries",
  "summary": "A CSS query container can be queried based on its container-name only, and the container does not need any container-type set:\n\n<style>\n#container {\n  container-name: --foo;\n}\n@container --foo {\n  input { background-color: green; }\n}\n<style>\n<div id=\"container\">\n  <div><input></div>\n</div>\n\nPreviously, @container required some query in addition to the name.\n",
